                                                    {
                                                    "question_English": "What are the different paths to spiritual liberation mentioned in the Bhagavad Gita?",
                                                    "answer_English": "The Bhagavad Gita discusses three main paths to spiritual liberation, known as yoga. These paths are Karma Yoga, Bhakti Yoga, and Jnana Yoga. Karma Yoga is the path of selfless action and emphasizes the importance of performing one's duties without attachment to the results. It teaches that by dedicating one's actions to a higher power and surrendering the fruits of those actions, one can attain spiritual growth and liberation. Bhakti Yoga is the path of devotion and love towards a personal deity or god. It involves surrendering oneself completely to the divine and cultivating a deep sense of love and devotion. Jnana Yoga is the path of knowledge and wisdom. It involves self-inquiry and the pursuit of knowledge to understand the true nature of the self and the universe. Through the cultivation of knowledge and the realization of one's true nature as the eternal soul, one can attain liberation from the cycle of birth and death.",
                                                    "question_Hindi": "भगवद्गीता में आध्यात्मिक मुक्ति के विभिन्न मार्ग क्या हैं?",
